<TITLE> Durga Puja gets off to colourful start </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 17 (bdnews24.com) -- Durga puja, the greatest religious festival of the Hindu community, took off Wednesday. The start of the colourful five-day celebrations was marked by reading from religious texts. The main arrangement has been in the central puja mandap, Dhakeshwari National Temple, in the capital. Devotees thronged the temple from morning. The other significant puja spots are Jagannath Hall at Dhaka University, Ramakrishna Mission, Ramna Kali Mondir, Anandamayi Ashram and Lokhnath Brahmmachari Ashram. bdnews24.
